= Addressing the Agricultrural Situation

The Azana government's land reform efforts have been met with... mixed reception. On one hand, the land owners and rentiers are dissatisfied with the concessions made to the land workers, the mixed juries and the wage increases. On the other haned, the land workers expected more from a government with the partcipation of the Socialists than mere half measures. Even before the Republic there has been talks of land redistribution and removal of the local caciques - corrupt officials who through police and armed thugs dominate the rural areas. The consolidation of the land workers into one region additionaly will hurt not only the seasonal workers' survival, but also the harvesting of the produce. 
Thus, many land workers have decided to organize and ask for what they deserve. Some have even joined the UGT and the socialist union has welcomed them, no doubt to wield them as influential weapon in their fight for power.
What shall we do? Do we support these workers and how do we do it?

- @revolutionary: We are all comrades in the war against oppression!
- @unionist: We should proclaim limited support for reforms.
