The land workers are also subjects of exploitation, a remnant of the old feudal order. Thus the National Committee, in accordance, with the union members' will, has decided to proclaim solidarity with all land workers and to invite them to the union untill land redstribution has been issued and the caciques' power is abolished.

@unionist
subtitle: We should proclaim limited support for reforms.
on-arrival:  unionist_strength += 10; reformist_strength += 5; revolutionary_dissent += 5; agri_union += 1; intellectual_dissent += 5; psoe_relation += 10;

The land workers' demands are reasonable and we should support them. Yet, it would be equally unreasonable to allienate the still-too-strong reactionary forces in Spain and doom all our hard-earned triumphs of the Republic. Thus, we shall stand only with those of the workers who ask for reasonable demands like wage increases and increased participation in the mixed juries, for we are not ready yet for a true land reform. 

